<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id7845d5e1-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s565a–3"><num value="565a–3">§ 565a–3.</num><heading> Agreements otherwise authorized by law</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Nothing in sections 565a–1 to 565a–3 of this title shall be construed as limiting or modifying the authority of the Secretary to enter into cooperative agreements otherwise authorized by law.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id7845d5e2-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/pl/94/148/s3">Pub. L. 94–148, § 3</ref>, <date date="1975-12-12">Dec. 12, 1975</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/89/804">89 Stat. 804</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
